<html xmlns:o="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" xmlns:x="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:excel" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40">
<head><meta charset="UTF-8"><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml><x:ExcelWorkbook><x:ExcelWorksheets><x:ExcelWorksheet><x:Name>TestResults</x:Name></x:ExcelWorksheet></x:ExcelWorksheets></x:ExcelWorkbook></xml><![endif]-->
<style>
  table { border-collapse: collapse; font-family: 'Segoe UI',Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; }
  th { background: #1F4E79; color: #fff; font-weight: bold; padding: 6px 10px; border: 1px solid #999; text-align: left; }
  td { padding: 4px 8px; border: 1px solid #ccc; vertical-align: top; }
  .pass { background: #C6EFCE; color: #006100; }
  .fail { background: #FFC7CE; color: #9C0006; }
  .suite1 { background: #E2EFDA; }
  .suite2 { background: #DAEEF3; }
  .suite3 { background: #FDE9D9; }
  .suite4 { background: #E4DFEC; }
  .suite5 { background: #FFFFCC; }
  .summary { background: #1F4E79; color: #fff; font-weight: bold; }
  .summary td { background: #1F4E79; color: #fff; font-weight: bold; border: 1px solid #999; }
  tr:hover td { background: #F2F2F2; }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<table>
<tr><th>Lp.</th><th>Suita</th><th>Test</th><th>Status</th><th>Czas (ms)</th><th>Opis</th></tr>

<!-- Known Issue #1 -->
<tr class="suite1"><td>1</td><td rowspan="4">Known Issue #1 (fixed) — MTTR label corrected to hours</td><td>q11label uses "hrs" (time unit) instead of "{C}" (currency)</td><td class="pass">PASS</td><td>2.0099</td><td>FIX APPLIED: q11label="MTTR (hrs)" — no longer uses {C}</td></tr>
<tr class="suite1"><td>2</td><td>q11label is now consistent with q4label — q4 uses {C}/h (cost), q11 uses hrs (time)</td><td class="pass">PASS</td><td>0.3012</td><td>q11 uses hrs, q4 uses {C}/h — no ambiguity between time and cost labels</td></tr>
<tr class="suite1"><td>3</td><td>q11 HASH_CONSTRAINTS max=168 confirms the unit is hours (1 week), not currency</td><td class="pass">PASS</td><td>0.3215</td><td>q11 max is 168 hours (= 1 week), proving MTTR is a time value, not monetary</td></tr>
<tr class="suite1"><td>4</td><td>Risk formula is dimensionally correct</td><td class="pass">PASS</td><td>0.3195</td><td>Formula: (8 failures × 4 hrs × $5000/hr) × (3/5) = $96000 — dimensionally sound</td></tr>

<!-- Known Issue #2 -->
<tr class="suite2"><td>5</td><td rowspan="3">Known Issue #2 — OPEX Waste appears 2.5× in Total Debt Impact</td><td>cCascade = cWaste × 0.5 ⇒ OPEX contributes indirectly via cascade (reduced)</td><td class="pass">PASS</td><td>0.3528</td><td>cCascade = $500k × 0.5 = $250k — reduced multiplier to avoid double-counting</td></tr>
<tr class="suite2"><td>6</td><td>totalImpact = cWaste + cRisk + cOppDirect + cCascade — cascade no longer dominates</td><td class="pass">PASS</td><td>0.2279</td><td>Total = 500k + 80k + 25k + 250k = $855,000</td></tr>
<tr class="suite2"><td>7</td><td>Main payback savings base now matches scenario savings — both include cascade (fixed)</td><td class="pass">PASS</td><td>0.3742</td><td>Both main payback and scenarios use (cWaste + cRisk + cCascade) × autoLevel = $498k/yr</td></tr>

<!-- Known Issue #3 -->
<tr class="suite3"><td>8</td><td rowspan="8">Known Issue #3 — Hardcoded coefficients without direct empirical basis</td><td>Pipeline erosion rate default = 0.25 (25%)</td><td class="pass">PASS</td><td>1.3042</td><td>Tool estimate — no single authoritative study isolates this fraction</td></tr>
<tr class="suite3"><td>9</td><td>Cascade multiplier default = 0.5 (reduced from 1.5)</td><td class="pass">PASS</td><td>0.2699</td><td>Reduced from 1.5 to avoid OPEX double-counting</td></tr>
<tr class="suite3"><td>10</td><td>Scenario C: auto level = 80%, CAPEX multiplier = 1.5</td><td class="pass">PASS</td><td>0.2682</td><td>Model assumptions, not externally sourced</td></tr>
<tr class="suite3"><td>11</td><td>Lever recovery rates: 30%, 60%, 50%, 15%, 30%</td><td class="pass">PASS</td><td>0.3714</td><td>Fixed percentages from varied sources</td></tr>
<tr class="suite3"><td>12</td><td>AUTOMATABLE_SHARE = 60%</td><td class="pass">PASS</td><td>0.2209</td><td>Cited in DevOps literature without specific source</td></tr>
<tr class="suite3"><td>13</td><td>TARGET_RISK_REDUCTION = 50%</td><td class="pass">PASS</td><td>0.2688</td><td>Model assumption for heatmap visualization</td></tr>
<tr class="suite3"><td>14</td><td>Annual hours = 1800, Turnover ref hours = 1800</td><td class="pass">PASS</td><td>1.7613</td><td>Aligned to same standard (1800h)</td></tr>
<tr class="suite3"><td>15</td><td>Recommendation gate thresholds: all set to 0</td><td class="pass">PASS</td><td>0.1354</td><td>Always show when > 0</td></tr>

<!-- Known Issue #4 -->
<tr class="suite4"><td>16</td><td rowspan="11">Known Issue #4 (mitigated) — NPV model verifies fix is in place</td><td>COEFFICIENTS contains DISCOUNT_RATE_DEFAULT and TIME_HORIZON_YEARS_DEFAULT</td><td class="pass">PASS</td><td>0.2585</td><td>Discount rate = 10% (WACC benchmark), Time horizon = 5 years</td></tr>
<tr class="suite4"><td>17</td><td>NPV recurring = annualRecurring × PVIFA(10%, 5yr) — annuity formula</td><td class="pass">PASS</td><td>0.1824</td><td>NPV of $830k/yr × PVIFA ≈ $3,146,353 — correctly discounts future cash flows</td></tr>
<tr class="suite4"><td>18</td><td>NPV total = one-time costs + NPV of recurring costs</td><td class="pass">PASS</td><td>0.1505</td><td>NPV Total = one-time costs + discounted recurring stream</td></tr>
<tr class="suite4"><td>19</td><td>Discounted payback > simple payback (time value of money extends payback)</td><td class="pass">PASS</td><td>0.2238</td><td>Discounted payback ≥ simple payback — TVM extends payback</td></tr>
<tr class="suite4"><td>20</td><td>DiscountedPayback returns Infinity for zero savings</td><td class="pass">PASS</td><td>0.2087</td><td>Edge case: zero savings → Infinity</td></tr>
<tr class="suite4"><td>21</td><td>DiscountedPayback returns Infinity for zero investment</td><td class="pass">PASS</td><td>0.2173</td><td>Edge case: zero investment → Infinity</td></tr>
<tr class="suite4"><td>22</td><td>DiscountedPayback returns Infinity when savings never cover investment</td><td class="pass">PASS</td><td>0.1686</td><td>Edge case: small savings vs large investment → Infinity</td></tr>
<tr class="suite4"><td>23</td><td>Single-year totalImpact still available for waterfall chart compatibility</td><td class="pass">PASS</td><td>0.1285</td><td>Single-year totalImpact = $855,000 — kept for legacy display</td></tr>
<tr class="suite4"><td>24</td><td>IRR > WACC for a profitable investment</td><td class="pass">PASS</td><td>0.7401</td><td>IRR should exceed WACC (10%) for value creation</td></tr>
<tr class="suite4"><td>25</td><td>IRR is meaningless (null or &lt; -90%) for all-negative cash flows</td><td class="pass">PASS</td><td>0.3167</td><td>All-negative flows have no meaningful IRR</td></tr>
<tr class="suite4"><td>26</td><td>IRR = 0 for zero-NPV investment (break-even)</td><td class="pass">PASS</td><td>0.3949</td><td>Break-even IRR ≈ 0%</td></tr>

<!-- Known Issue #5 -->
<tr class="suite5"><td>27</td><td rowspan="11">Known Issue #5 — Runtime integrity: calculate() logic audit</td><td>cRisk uses MTTR (q11) as hours — dimensionally correct at runtime</td><td class="pass">PASS</td><td>0.5403</td><td>cRisk = (8 failures × 4hrs × $5k/hr) × (3/5) = $96k — MTTR as hours</td></tr>
<tr class="suite5"><td>28</td><td>cRisk scales linearly with MTTR — time multiplier, not currency</td><td class="pass">PASS</td><td>0.2065</td><td>Doubling MTTR (2→8 hrs) quadruples cRisk — MTTR is a linear time multiplier</td></tr>
<tr class="suite5"><td>29</td><td>totalImpact = cWaste + cRisk + cOppDirect + cCascade (no hidden OPEX terms)</td><td class="pass">PASS</td><td>0.2170</td><td>totalImpact is exactly the sum of 4 terms</td></tr>
<tr class="suite5"><td>30</td><td>cCascade = cWaste × cascadeMult (default 0.5) — OPEX contributes at most 1.5×</td><td class="pass">PASS</td><td>0.2351</td><td>cCascade = cWaste × 0.5 — OPEX does not dominate beyond 95%</td></tr>
<tr class="suite5"><td>31</td><td>Scenario A (Do Nothing) savings = 0 — no unintended OPEX leakage</td><td class="pass">PASS</td><td>0.1547</td><td>With autoLevel=0, potentialSavings = $0 — no phantom savings</td></tr>
<tr class="suite5"><td>32</td><td>Overriding cascadeMult to 1.0 doubles cCascade vs default 0.5</td><td class="pass">PASS</td><td>0.1638</td><td>cCascade at 1.0 = 2× cCascade at 0.5 — slider override works</td></tr>
<tr class="suite5"><td>33</td><td>Overriding erosionRate to 0 halves cOppDirect</td><td class="pass">PASS</td><td>0.2180</td><td>With erosionRate=0, cOppDirect = $0</td></tr>
<tr class="suite5"><td>34</td><td>NPV total = oneTimeCosts + annualRecurring × PVIFA(discountRate, horizonYears)</td><td class="pass">PASS</td><td>0.2071</td><td>npvTotalDebt matches PVIFA formula</td></tr>
<tr class="suite5"><td>35</td><td>Discount rate of 0% collapses PVIFA to plain n-years (no discounting)</td><td class="pass">PASS</td><td>0.2231</td><td>At 0% discount, NPV = oneTime + annualRecurring × 5</td></tr>
<tr class="suite5"><td>36</td><td>Longer horizon increases NPV total (more recurring years counted)</td><td class="pass">PASS</td><td>0.2939</td><td>NPV at 10yr horizon > NPV at 3yr horizon</td></tr>
<tr class="suite5"><td>37</td><td>Higher WACC lowers NPV (time value of money)</td><td class="pass">PASS</td><td>0.1738</td><td>NPV at 15% WACC < NPV at 5% WACC</td></tr>

